en minutes elapsed. No, my agitation refused to keep seated. Moreover, I was out of cigarettes and craved frantically for a smoke.

I turned into a side street, passing, as I did so, a black Protestant church which affected an air of antiquity, and espied a tobacconist’s. The automatic bell continued to whirr after my entering, as I had not closed the door: “Will you please—” said the bespectacled woman behind the counter, and I stepped back and shut the door sharply. Just above it was o